 2204              ref node => {
 2205                  cx.sess.span_warn(warning_span, fmt!("debuginfo::get_namespace_and_span_for_item() \
 2206                                                        - Unexpected node type: %?", *node));
 2207                  codemap::dummy_sp()
 2208              }
 2209          };
 2210          (containing_scope, definition_span)
 2211      } else {
 2212          let item_path = ty::item_path(cx.tcx, def_id);
 2213          // For external items there is no span information
 2214          (namespace_for_external_item(cx, &item_path).scope, codemap::dummy_sp())
 2215      }
 2216  }
 2217  
 2218  // This procedure builds the *scope map* for a given function, which maps any given ast::NodeId in
 2219  // the function's AST to the correct DIScope metadata instance.
 2220  //
 2221  // This builder procedure walks the AST in execution order and keeps track of what belongs to which
 2222  // scope, creating DIScope DIEs along the way, and introducing *artificial* lexical scope
 2223  // descriptors where necessary. These artificial scopes allow GDB to correctly handle name
 2224  // shadowing.
 2225  fn populate_scope_map(cx: &mut CrateContext,
 2226                        arg_pats: &[@ast::Pat],
 2227                        fn_entry_block: &ast::Block,
 2228                        fn_metadata: DISubprogram,
 2229                        scope_map: &mut HashMap<ast::NodeId, DIScope>) {
 2230      let def_map = cx.tcx.def_map;
 2231  
 2232      struct ScopeStackEntry {
 2233          scope_metadata: DIScope,
 2234          ident: Option<ast::Ident>
 2235      }
 2236  
 2237      let mut scope_stack = ~[ScopeStackEntry { scope_metadata: fn_metadata, ident: None }];
 2238  
 2239      // Push argument identifiers onto the stack so arguments integrate nicely with variable
 2240      // shadowing.
 2241      for &arg_pat in arg_pats.iter() {
 2242          do pat_util::pat_bindings(def_map, arg_pat) |_, _, _, path_ref| {
 2243              let ident = ast_util::path_to_ident(path_ref);
 2244              scope_stack.push(ScopeStackEntry { scope_metadata: fn_metadata, ident: Some(ident) });
 2245          }
 2246      }
 2247  
 2248      walk_block(cx, fn_entry_block, &mut scope_stack, scope_map);
 2249  
 2250      // local helper functions for walking the AST.
 2251      fn with_new_scope(cx: &mut CrateContext,
 2252                        scope_span: Span,
 2253                        scope_stack: &mut ~[ScopeStackEntry],
 2254                        scope_map: &mut HashMap<ast::NodeId, DIScope>,
 2255                        inner_walk: &fn(&mut CrateContext,
 2256                                        &mut ~[ScopeStackEntry],
 2257                                        &mut HashMap<ast::NodeId, DIScope>)) {
 2258          // Create a new lexical scope and push it onto the stack
 2259          let loc = cx.sess.codemap.lookup_char_pos(scope_span.lo);
 2260          let file_metadata = file_metadata(cx, loc.file.name);
 2261          let parent_scope = scope_stack.last().scope_metadata;
 2262  
 2263          let scope_metadata = unsafe {
 2264              llvm::LLVMDIBuilderCreateLexicalBlock(
 2265                  DIB(cx),
 2266                  parent_scope,
 2267                  file_metadata,
 2268                  loc.line as c_uint,
 2269                  loc.col.to_uint() as c_uint)
 2270          };
 2271  
 2272          scope_stack.push(ScopeStackEntry { scope_metadata: scope_metadata, ident: None });
 2273  
 2274          inner_walk(cx, scope_stack, scope_map);
 2275  
 2276          // pop artificial scopes
 2277          while scope_stack.last().ident.is_some() {
 2278              scope_stack.pop();
 2279          }
 2280  
 2281          if scope_stack.last().scope_metadata != scope_metadata {
 2282              cx.sess.span_bug(scope_span, "debuginfo: Inconsistency in scope management.");
 2283          }
 2284  
 2285          scope_stack.pop();
 2286      }
 2287  
 2288      fn walk_block(cx: &mut CrateContext,
 2289                    block: &ast::Block,
 2290                    scope_stack: &mut ~[ScopeStackEntry],
 2291                    scope_map: &mut HashMap<ast::NodeId, DIScope>) {
 2292          scope_map.insert(block.id, scope_stack.last().scope_metadata);
 2293  
 2294          // The interesting things here are statements and the concluding expression.
 2295          for &@ ref statement in block.stmts.iter() {
 2296              scope_map.insert(ast_util::stmt_id(statement), scope_stack.last().scope_metadata);
 2297  
 2298              match statement.node {
 2299                  ast::StmtDecl(@ref decl, _) => walk_decl(cx, decl, scope_stack, scope_map),
 2300                  ast::StmtExpr(@ref exp, _) |
 2301                  ast::StmtSemi(@ref exp, _) => walk_expr(cx, exp, scope_stack, scope_map),
 2302                  ast::StmtMac(*) => () // ignore macros (which should be expanded anyway)
 2303              }
 2304          }
 2305  
 2306          for &@ref exp in block.expr.iter() {
 2307              walk_expr(cx, exp, scope_stack, scope_map);
 2308          }
 2309      }
 2310  
 2311      fn walk_decl(cx: &mut CrateContext,
 2312                   decl: &ast::Decl,
 2313                   scope_stack: &mut ~[ScopeStackEntry],
 2314                   scope_map: &mut HashMap<ast::NodeId, DIScope>) {
 2315          match *decl {
 2316              codemap::Spanned { node: ast::DeclLocal(@ref local), _ } => {
 2317                  scope_map.insert(local.id, scope_stack.last().scope_metadata);
 2318  
 2319                  walk_pattern(cx, local.pat, scope_stack, scope_map);
 2320  
 2321                  for &@ref exp in local.init.iter() {
 2322                      walk_expr(cx, exp, scope_stack, scope_map);
 2323                  }
 2324              }
 2325              _ => ()
 2326          }
 2327      }
 2328  
 2329      fn walk_pattern(cx: &mut CrateContext,
 2330                      pat: @ast::Pat,
 2331                      scope_stack: &mut ~[ScopeStackEntry],
 2332                      scope_map: &mut HashMap<ast::NodeId, DIScope>) {
 2333  
 2334          let def_map = cx.tcx.def_map;
 2335  
 2336          // Unfortunately, we cannot just use pat_util::pat_bindings() or ast_util::walk_pat() here
 2337          // because we have to visit *all* nodes in order to put them into the scope map. The above
 2338          // functions don't do that.
 2339          match pat.node {
 2340              ast::PatIdent(_, ref path_ref, ref sub_pat_opt) => {
 2341  
 2342                  // Check if this is a binding. If so we need to put it on the scope stack and maybe
 2343                  // introduce an articial scope
 2344                  if pat_util::pat_is_binding(def_map, pat) {
 2345  
 2346                      let ident = ast_util::path_to_ident(path_ref);
 2347  
 2348                      // LLVM does not properly generate 'DW_AT_start_scope' fields for variable DIEs.
 2349                      // For this reason we have to introduce an artificial scope at bindings whenever
 2350                      // a variable with the same name is declared in *any* parent scope.
 2351                      //
 2352                      // Otherwise the following error occurs:
 2353                      //
 2354                      // let x = 10;
 2355                      //
 2356                      // do_something(); // 'gdb print x' correctly prints 10
 2357                      //
 2358                      // {
 2359                      //     do_something(); // 'gdb print x' prints 0, because it already reads the
 2360                      //                     // uninitialized 'x' from the next line...
 2361                      //     let x = 100;
 2362                      //     do_something(); // 'gdb print x' correctly prints 100
 2363                      // }
 2364  
 2365                      // Is there already a binding with that name?
 2366                      // N.B.: this comparison must be UNhygienic... because
 2367                      // gdb knows nothing about the context, so any two
 2368                      // variables with the same name will cause the problem.
 2369                      let need_new_scope = scope_stack
 2370                          .iter()
 2371                          .any(|entry| entry.ident.iter().any(|i| i.name == ident.name));
 2372  
 2373                      if need_new_scope {
 2374                          // Create a new lexical scope and push it onto the stack
 2375                          let loc = cx.sess.codemap.lookup_char_pos(pat.span.lo);
 2376                          let file_metadata = file_metadata(cx, loc.file.name);
 2377                          let parent_scope = scope_stack.last().scope_metadata;
 2378  
 2379                          let scope_metadata = unsafe {
 2380                              llvm::LLVMDIBuilderCreateLexicalBlock(
 2381                                  DIB(cx),
 2382                                  parent_scope,
 2383                                  file_metadata,
 2384                                  loc.line as c_uint,
 2385                                  loc.col.to_uint() as c_uint)
 2386                          };
 2387  
 2388                          scope_stack.push(ScopeStackEntry {
 2389                              scope_metadata: scope_metadata,
 2390                              ident: Some(ident)
 2391                          });
 2392  
 2393                      } else {
 2394                          // Push a new entry anyway so the name can be found
 2395                          let prev_metadata = scope_stack.last().scope_metadata;
 2396                          scope_stack.push(ScopeStackEntry {
 2397                              scope_metadata: prev_metadata,
 2398                              ident: Some(ident)
 2399                          });
 2400                      }
 2401                  }
 2402  
 2403                  scope_map.insert(pat.id, scope_stack.last().scope_metadata);
 2404  
 2405                  for &sub_pat in sub_pat_opt.iter() {
 2406                      walk_pattern(cx, sub_pat, scope_stack, scope_map);
 2407                  }
 2408              }
 2409  
 2410              ast::PatWild => {
 2411                  scope_map.insert(pat.id, scope_stack.last().scope_metadata);
 2412              }
 2413  
 2414              ast::PatEnum(_, ref sub_pats_opt) => {
 2415                  scope_map.insert(pat.id, scope_stack.last().scope_metadata);
 2416  
 2417                  for ref sub_pats in sub_pats_opt.iter() {
 2418                      for &p in sub_pats.iter() {
 2419                          walk_pattern(cx, p, scope_stack, scope_map);
 2420                      }
 2421                  }
 2422              }
 2423  
 2424              ast::PatStruct(_, ref field_pats, _) => {
 2425                  scope_map.insert(pat.id, scope_stack.last().scope_metadata);
 2426  
 2427                  for &ast::FieldPat { pat: sub_pat, _ } in field_pats.iter() {
 2428                      walk_pattern(cx, sub_pat, scope_stack, scope_map);
 2429                  }
 2430              }
 2431  
 2432              ast::PatTup(ref sub_pats) => {
 2433                  scope_map.insert(pat.id, scope_stack.last().scope_metadata);
 2434  
 2435                  for &sub_pat in sub_pats.iter() {
 2436                      walk_pattern(cx, sub_pat, scope_stack, scope_map);
 2437                  }
 2438              }
 2439  
 2440              ast::PatBox(sub_pat)    |
 2441              ast::PatUniq(sub_pat)   |
 2442              ast::PatRegion(sub_pat) => {

 2444                  walk_pattern(cx, sub_pat, scope_stack, scope_map);
 2445              }
 2446  
 2447              ast::PatLit(@ref exp) => {
 2448                  scope_map.insert(pat.id, scope_stack.last().scope_metadata);
 2449                  walk_expr(cx, exp, scope_stack, scope_map);
 2450              }
 2451  
 2452              ast::PatRange(@ref exp1, @ref exp2) => {
 2453                  scope_map.insert(pat.id, scope_stack.last().scope_metadata);
 2454                  walk_expr(cx, exp1, scope_stack, scope_map);
 2455                  walk_expr(cx, exp2, scope_stack, scope_map);
 2456              }
 2457  
 2458              ast::PatVec(ref front_sub_pats, ref middle_sub_pats, ref back_sub_pats) => {
 2459                  scope_map.insert(pat.id, scope_stack.last().scope_metadata);
 2460  
 2461                  for &sub_pat in front_sub_pats.iter() {
 2462                      walk_pattern(cx, sub_pat, scope_stack, scope_map);
 2463                  }
 2464  
 2465                  for &sub_pat in middle_sub_pats.iter() {
 2466                      walk_pattern(cx, sub_pat, scope_stack, scope_map);
 2467                  }
 2468  
 2469                  for &sub_pat in back_sub_pats.iter() {
 2470                      walk_pattern(cx, sub_pat, scope_stack, scope_map);
 2471                  }
 2472              }
 2473          }
 2474      }

 2476      fn walk_expr(cx: &mut CrateContext,
 2477                   exp: &ast::Expr,
 2478                   scope_stack: &mut ~[ScopeStackEntry],
 2479                   scope_map: &mut HashMap<ast::NodeId, DIScope>) {
 2480  
 2481          scope_map.insert(exp.id, scope_stack.last().scope_metadata);
 2482  
 2483          match exp.node {
 2484              ast::ExprLogLevel |
 2485              ast::ExprSelf     |
 2486              ast::ExprLit(_)   |
 2487              ast::ExprBreak(_) |

 2490

 2496

 2498                  Some(@ref sub_exp) => walk_expr(cx, sub_exp, scope_stack, scope_map),
 2499                  None => ()
 2500              },

 2714      let last_index = path_excluding_item.len() - 1;

 2724

 2727              Some(existing_node) => existing_node,
 2728              None => {
 2729                  // create and insert
 2730                  let parent_scope = match parent_node {
 2731                      Some(node) => node.scope,
 2732                      None => ptr::null()
 2733                  };

 2741                              namespace_name,

 2744                      }
